Ques: How to configure message delivery in Apache kafka ?
Ans: Message delivery in Kafka is guaranteed using at-least-once or exactly-once semantics. At-least-once is achieved using acks=all, retries, replication, and manual offset commits. Exactly-once is
achieved using Kafka transactions with idempotent producers and transactional consumers. Additionally, retry mechanisms and dead letter queues ensure no message is lost even in failure scenarios.

ack = all means The producer waits until ALL in-sync replicas (ISR - replicas that are fully synced in leader followr partitions) acknowledge the message before marking it as successful. Ensures durability 
even broker fails. If there is no confirmation message will not be committed.

